{"sections":[],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"enum"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"DiskInjector"}],"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"anchor":"overview","text":"Overview","type":"heading","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Before the VM boots, ","type":"text"},{"code":"DiskInjector","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" mounts the guest disk image on the host,","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"writes a standard macOS LaunchDaemon plist and the user’s script to the data","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"volume, then unmounts. When the VM boots, ","type":"text"},{"code":"launchd","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" picks up the daemon and","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"executes the script automatically — no SSH, no agent, no network required."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"This uses Apple’s ","type":"text"},{"code":"hdiutil","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" (ships with macOS) to attach APFS disk images"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"and writes only to the data volume (never the Signed System Volume)."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"level":2,"type":"heading","anchor":"Usage","text":"Usage"},{"code":["let scriptURL = URL(fileURLWithPath: \"\/path\/to\/setup.sh\")","let bundle = try VirtualMachineBundle.load(from: bundleURL)","try DiskInjector.inject(script: scriptURL, into: bundle)"],"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing"},{"level":2,"type":"heading","anchor":"How-It-Works","text":"How It Works"},{"type":"orderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Attaches the guest’s "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"disk.img"},{"type":"text","text":" using "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"hdiutil"},{"type":"text","text":" without mounting"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"(to discover the device node)."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Finds and mounts the APFS data volume from the attached disk."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Writes the user’s script to "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"\/usr\/local\/bin\/spooktacular-user-data.sh"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"on the data volume."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Writes a LaunchDaemon plist to "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"\/Library\/LaunchDaemons\/"},{"type":"text","text":" that tells"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"launchd"},{"type":"text","text":" to run the script at boot."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Detaches the disk image so the VM can boot cleanly."}]}]}]},{"level":2,"type":"heading","anchor":"Thread-Safety","text":"Thread Safety"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"All methods are synchronous and use "},{"code":"Process","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" to invoke "},{"code":"hdiutil","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Call from a background thread if needed to avoid blocking the main thread."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"minor":3,"major":0},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit"]]},"kind":"symbol","identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/DiskInjector","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/spooktacularkit\/diskinjector"]}],"metadata":{"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"enum"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"DiskInjector","kind":"identifier"}],"role":"symbol","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"DiskInjector"}],"modules":[{"name":"SpooktacularKit"}],"roleHeading":"Enumeration","externalID":"s:15